== Usage ==
<strong>This template is designed for use by {{tl|Taxobox/core}}, and should not be called directly.</strong>

<code><nowiki>{{</nowiki>Taxobox/species|''status system parameter''|''conservation status parameter''|extinction_date=''value''}}</code>

Returns the conservation code coloured circles and adds categories. {{para|extinction_date}} is passed from taxoboxes for species, e.g. {{tl|Speciesbox}}, where it is set by {{para|extinct}}. If its value is not empty, "yes" or "true", it should be an indication of the date when the species became extinct, e.g. "1510" or "after 1791" or "about 1800". It will be shown after the word "Extinct", as in the first example below.

;Examples
* <nowiki>{{Taxobox/species | IUCN2.3 | EX |extinction_date=about 1620}}</nowiki>
* <nowiki>{{Taxobox/species |TNC |T5 }}</nowiki>
* <nowiki>{{Taxobox/species |IUCN3.1 |EX }}</nowiki>

